        http://fvwm-nightshade.github.com/Fvwm-Nightshade

        
Welcome to Fvwm-Nightshade! This project aims to be a lightweight but
feature rich and good looking configuration of Fvwm. It contains many 
useful things to make work and life easier with a flavour of a modern 
desktop. But it can be also configured by your own. It's good documented
and shows you what is possible with this powerful window manager.

***********************************************************************
************* ATTENTION: THIS IS A DEVELOPMENT VERSION!   *************
*************            CURRENTLY IT WORKS !             *************
***********************************************************************

Featurelist of Fvwm-Nightshade 0.7.x:
=====================================
- Works with FVWM 2.6.5 but with full support of Xdg menus like in 
  CVS version of FVWM.

- Own user configuration directory ~/.fvwm-nightshade (can be used 
  parallel to existing Fvwm configuration).
- Own entry "Fvwm-Nightshade" in graphical login managers.
- Own XDG applications menu with it's own directory files.

- Build support for deb, rpm, Gentoo and Arch installation.
- Support for local installation without root rights.
- Localization support for German, French, Spanish and Russian.

- Support for shadows and transparency with XcompMgr and Compton.
- Support for hald, upower and systemd for Suspend and Hibernate.
- Support for hotplug mounting (i.e. usb).
- Support for icons on desktop. Also for mounted devices.

- Up to 10 virtual desktop pages (more possible but only keys 0-9 
  for different key bindings are available).
- Taskbar to show running apps per page.
- Lock desk & screen (xscreensaver).
- Autostart possibility (starting apps while startup).

- Gtk2 Config tools for different settings:
  - FNS-BaseSetup (layouts, themes, compositing, icons on desktop, etc.).
  - FNS-WindowsBehaviour (focus policies, placement, etc.).
  - FNS-CompConfigurator (config tool for xcompmgr or compton).
  - FNS-MenuConfigurator (exchange original fvwm-menu-config GUI).
  - FNS-CPU-Performance (governor-tool for cpufreq / cpupower).
  - FNS-MenuBuilder (configuration tool for personal menu).

- "Run" command depending on installed software (grun, gmrun or FvwmForm).
- Background configurable with a thumb browser which can scan different
  wallpaper locations.

- Four different layouts scalable up to 4K:
  - horizontal (top)
  - vertical (top right)
  - G2like (top & bottom)
  - Klike (bottom)

- Many eye candy themes/decors (changable on the fly without restart):
  - Air
  - Ambience
  - Clean
  - CrystalBalls
  - FlatTab
  - GrayRevenge
  - PitchBlack (default)
  - Redmond 
  - Rocken
  - Tribal

- Own Gtk2 and 3 themes for Air, Tribal, FlatTab and PitchBlack (default).
- Set of nice icons for menus and internal apps.

- Animation control of window moves (FvwmAnimate).
- Window focus switching with Alt-Tab / Shift-Alt-Tab.
- Animated Splash screen (in progress).
- Creation of thumbs with mini icon and name for iconified applications 
  instead of a simple icon.
- Smart maximize windows - move and resize windows to the largest free 
  area of a desktop page.

- Dynamic menus
- Help messages for mouse bindings in titlebar, window, corners, sides.
- Help messages for key bindings.


Requirements:
=============
Required:       Fvwm >= 2.6.5, python-2.7, python-xdg, xterm, conky, 
                xscreensaver, feh, imagemagick, librsvg2-bin, xwd,
                stalonetray, cpufrequtils or cpupower, gksu, pcmanfm,
                libgtk2-perl, liblocale-gettext-perl, polkit-gnome

Recommended:    gnome-network-manager, pm-utils, qtconfig for qt4, 
                lxappearance, gtk2-engines-murrine, gtk2-engines-pixbuf

Suggested:      fdpowermon or cbatticon-gtk2 (for pm-utils), blueman, 
                grun or gmrun, volumeicon-alsa, clipit or parcelite, 
                xneur, compton or xcompmgr


Installation
============
For installation description see the INSTALL file.


Bugs and Feature requests
=========================
Fvwm-Nightshade is a young project. Bugs are possible. We try to avoid 
them but nobody is perfect ... So, if you find one or have ideas, submit
them under https://github.com/Fvwm-Nightshade/Fvwm-Nightshade/issues or
send an email to fvwmnightshade@gmail.com.


Mailinglist
===========
There exist two mailing lists under
common:        https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#!forum/fvwmnightshade
developing:    https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#!forum/fvwmnightshade-workers

To post to this group, you have to do the following:

1. Register your email at google by clicking on the "Sign in" button 
   (upper right side).
2. After successful email verification login to your new account.
3. Go to 
   https://groups.google.com/forum/?hl=en#!forum/fvwmnightshade 
   and click on button "Apply to join group".
4. Fill out the join form and click on "Apply to this group" button.
5. After your request is approved you get an email from us.
6. Now you can send email to fvwmnightshade@googlegroups.com to post to 
   the mailing list.

To unsubscribe from this group, send email to 
<fvwmnightshade+unsubscribe@googlegroups.com>
or
<fvwmnightshade-workers+unsubscribe@googlegroups.com>


Enjoy our work and hopefully you love Fvwm-Nightshade as we do :-)


